Bonjour à tous,

Vous trouverez ci-joint une offre de thèse CIFRE proposée par
SAP et le Laboratoire d'Informatique de l'Université de Tours.
Merci de diffuser à toute personne intéressée.

Cordialement,
Patrick Marcel.




The BdTln research group of the Computer Sciences Labs of the University 
of Tours (located in Blois) and SAP Labs France (located in 
Levallois-Perret) propose a 3 years fully funded PhD position on 
recommendation systems for Business Intelligence. The research project 
is to enrich SAP solutions for the exploration and analysis of large and 
heterogeneous data sources.


Detailed description of the PhD thesis:

This PhD thesis aims at developing new recommendation algorithms to help 
experienced or casual BI users to produce meaningful business-oriented 
analytics. To this aim, the proposed approach will consider methods from 
the Exploratory Search domain, which rely on the modeling and the 
evolution of a user profile enriched by business and applicative knowledge.


The objective is to provide dynamically the right analysis to the user 
paired with interesting visualizations. In other words, the analysis 
should take into account the semantic of business models, data from 
business applications and the context of the user.


The user context will be derived from its past activity like the 
navigation patterns, but also his/her preferences and information needs 
or the usage of visualizations based on the type of measures to represent.

In a more technical point of view, this PhD thesis will tackle the 
Exploratory Search problem as a multi-objective recommendation problem 
that will seemlessly propose keywords, filters, dimensions to build a 
query and then provides the user with interactive visualizations that 
match this specific user information needs.


The doctoral student will be supervised jointly by SAP Labs France and 
the BdTln research group. A good coding experience is required.


If you are interested, please contact ASAP one of the following:

